===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)ker-|id=cut}}
From {{inh|en|enm|sherte}}, {{m|enm|shurte}}, {{m|enm|schirte}}, from {{inh|en|ang|sċyrte||a short garment; skirt; kirtle}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*skurtijā}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*skurtijǭ|t=a short garment, skirt, apron}}.

Cognate with {{cog|stq|Schoarte|t=apron}}, {{cog|nl|schort|t=apron}}, {{cog|de|Schürze|t=apron}}, {{cog|da|skjorte|t=shirt}}, {{cog|no|skjorte|t=shirt}}, {{cog|sv|skjorta|t=shirt}}, {{cog|fo|skjúrta|t=shirt}}, {{cog|is|skyrta|t=shirt}}.

{{cog|en|skirt}} is a parallel formation from Old Norse; which is a {{doublet|en|short|nocap=1}}, from the same ultimate source.

